Genitalia: Two very long strongly curved, weakly sclerotized spermathecae, resembling an “M” with distal portion near spermathecal base (Fig. 
4
).

Color pattern: Carapace brown with golden hairs. Coxae, labium, sternum and maxillae black; trochantera to tarsi ventrally brown. Prolateral and retrolateral femora, patellae, tibiae and metatarsi of legs and palpi brown with metallic green/blue iridescence (Fig. A 
2
). Dorso-medial conspicuous orange stripe along all tarsi and sinuous on metatarsi (Figs A 
1
─A 
2
). Orange rings on distal tibiae and metatarsi (Fig. A 
1
). Abdomen black with brownish anterolateral areas, with some long red hairs (Fig. A 
1
).

Distribution: Southern State of Bahia, Brazil (
Fig. 17
).
